http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Probe-sought-into-deer-deaths/article13987212.ece

: Society for Prevention of Cruelty against Animals (SPCA) in Ernakulam has sought the intervention of National Zoo Authority and Animal Welfare Board into the deaths of spotted deer at the Deer Park in Hill Palace, Tripunithura here.T.K. Sajeev, its secretary, and T.M. Sajith, SPCA inspector, visited the site on Thursday. They demanded a probe by the authorities concerned in to the deaths of nearly five spotted deers at the park. They also claimed to have found the carcass of a deer with deep wounds in a bush in the deer park, they said.